
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `cd-iccdump` baraye khandan va namayesh dadan profile-haye ICC (International Color Consortium) az rooye CD-ROM ya file image CD estefade mishavad. In dastoor etela'ate rang ra ke dar file-haye ICC zakhire shode and, neshan midahad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `cd-iccdump -v`  --> 🗣️ Namayesh etela'at bishtar (verbose mode).
    🔹 `cd-iccdump -o <filename>` --> 💾 Zakhire kardan khuruji dar yek file be jaye namayesh dar terminal.
    🔹 `cd-iccdump <device>` --> 📍 Specify device CD-ROM (masalan /dev/cdrom).

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ cd-iccdump
    
    🔹 Namayesh profile ICC az CD-ROM pishfarz.

    $ cd-iccdump -o profile.icc /dev/cdrom
    
    🔹 Zakhire kardan profile ICC az device `/dev/cdrom` dar file `profile.icc`.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ cd-iccdump -v
    
    🔹 Namayesh profile ICC ba etela'at bishtar, mesle tag-ha va description-ha.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `cd-iccdump` command is used to read and display ICC (International Color Consortium) profiles from a CD-ROM or CD image file. This command shows the color information stored in the ICC files.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `cd-iccdump -v` --> 🗣️  Verbose mode, displaying more detailed information.
    🔹 `cd-iccdump -o <filename>` --> 💾 Save the output to a file instead of displaying it in the terminal.
    🔹 `cd-iccdump <device>` --> 📍 Specify the CD-ROM device (e.g., /dev/cdrom).

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ cd-iccdump
    
    🔹 Display the ICC profile from the default CD-ROM device.

    $ cd-iccdump -o profile.icc /dev/cdrom
    
    🔹 Save the ICC profile from the `/dev/cdrom` device to the `profile.icc` file.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ cd-iccdump -v
    
    🔹 Display the ICC profile with more detailed information, such as tags and descriptions.
